        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 3. Pholoides sinepapillatus sp. nov. (Holotype, IBUFRJ-3121) (A) Dorsal view of the anterior end; (B) Tentaculophore from right side (without dorsal cirrus); (C) Notochaeta; (D): Tip of same; (E) Style of dorsal cirrus of tentaculophore; (F) First elytra, right side; (G) Middle elytra, right side; (H) Parapodium from second segment; (I) Lower compound neurochaeta; (J): Upper compound neurochaeta; (K) Left middle elytrigerous parapodium. (Scales bars: A= 500 µm; B= 250 µm C= 50 µm, D, I and J= 150 µm and E= 75 µm; F, G, H and K = 300 µm)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4929881/files/figure.png" .

